{
  "text": "The analytical Michell frame solution (for a point load) was first derived by Chan (1960) and the normalized compliance value can be read from a table in [CITATION_1] . This value is \u03a6 = C/(f a) = 7.024707829 2 = 49.35, where a = 2 is the cantilever aspect ratio, f is the volume fraction and C is the compliance.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "122789771"
  },
